      "writtenOn": "2020-04-30T14:48:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, if the containers depend on absl::Mutex or dynamic_annotations, then this is fatal.  I\u0027d double check that, because if a container data structure really depends on absl::Mutex or dynamic_annotations, then that\u0027s an indication of poor design and a second reason to not use absl.\n\nabsl::Mutex is a crutch for Google3 developers used to its pre-standard behavior.  We already have to think about SkMutex, SkSharedMutex, SkSpinlock, std::mutex, inevitably std::shared_mutex, and often our clients\u0027 own locking abstractions... I will not allow any more that don\u0027t start \"std::\".",
      "parentUuid": "0ccba309_f7029d1e",
